%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G4.1: ACE field write side (CE-packet counting and
encoding). Both endpoints tcpEcnMode="accecn"; the client sends 200B of
data after the handshake completes, and the tcptester script marks that
data segment CE (IP_ECN_CE) on the wire. The server's independent
rcvCePkts counter (hooked at Tcp.cc's inbound EcnInd tag read, NOT routed
through the pre-existing, dead classic-ECN gotCeIndication flag -- see
description below) increments to 1, and its next outbound ACK encodes
ace = (1+5)&0x7 = 6 = 0b110 into (aeBit,cwrBit,eceBit) = (1,1,0), rendered
"W N" (no "E").

Also pins the connection-completing 3rd ACK (A002): building this test
caught a real ordering bug -- G3.1's SYN-ACK decode (which sets
accEcnNegotiated) originally ran AFTER tcpAlgorithm->established(true),
but established(true) is what synchronously sends the 3rd ACK, so that ACK
went out with accEcnNegotiated still false and no ACE encoding at all
(verified empirically: before the fix, A002 rendered as a plain "A ack 501"
with no ACE bits). Fixed by moving the ECN/AccECN decode block before
established(true) in processSegmentInSynSent() -- ordering that never
mattered for classic ECN, which doesn't touch this particular ACK's flags,
but matters here since AccECN's ACE field must already reflect the
just-negotiated state (matching the kernel's handling of the analogous
3rd-ACK case, tcp_accecn_3rd_ack_ce_updates_received_ce.pkt). A002 is
pinned below with ace=5=(0+5)&0x7 (rcvCePkts still 0 at that point) as the
regression check for this fix.

Falsification (the two code paths must be disjoint): verified empirically
by rerunning this exact scenario with tcpEcnMode="rfc3168" instead --
accEcnNegotiated never becomes true, so the CE mark on A003 produces no
ACE-style bit manipulation on B002 at all; the server's ACK shows only
classic ECN's own, unrelated ECE-echo bit ("E" alone, no "W"/"N").

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script="a3 ce"

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=0.5s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=200B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.*_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 3rd ACK of the handshake: ace=5=(0+5)&0x7 (rcvCePkts still 0) -- the ordering-bug regression check.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.005 A002] A.1000 > B.2000: A E N ack 501 win 7504
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's data segment, marked CE by the tester.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.501 A003] A.1000 > B.2000: A E N 1:201(200) ack 501 win 7504 # marking CE
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's ACK: ace=6=(1+5)&0x7, rendered W N (cwrBit+aeBit, no eceBit) -- the actual G4.1 assertion.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.503 B002] A.1000 < B.2000: A W N ack 201 win 7504
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
